@startuml
title Viaverse Matching — Data Flow Diagram

rectangle "ServiceRequest Snapshot\ncategory / budget / area / urgency" as Request
database "OpenSearch Provider/Business Index\ncategory / geo / services / public profile" as Index
database "Identity Eligibility\naccount status / capabilities / business team" as Identity
database "Trust Data\nrating / badges / risk / disputes / reports" as Trust
database "Valkey Hot State\navailability / rate limit / frequency cap" as HotState
component "Matching Ranker\ncandidate scoring + explanation" as Ranker
database "WorkerOpportunity Projection\nrequestId / targetId / score / reason codes" as Opportunity
component "Notification Inbox / Push\nnew matching opportunity" as Notification

Request --> Ranker : request features
Index --> Ranker : candidate docs
Identity --> Ranker : eligibility
Trust --> Ranker : trust/risk
HotState --> Ranker : availability
Ranker --> Opportunity : ranked opportunities
Opportunity --> Notification : notify

note bottom
OpenSearch, trust summaries and hot availability are read inputs.
The request source-of-truth remains marketplace-service/PostgreSQL.
end note
@enduml
